<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Computervision cut.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Computervision cut.</headline>
<text>
<p>-- Hambrecht &amp; Quist cut its rating and 1997 earnings estimate on Computervision Corp after it ended an agreement to sell its hardware services business to J.F. Lehman. Instead it will sell a 51-percent stake to investment manager M.D. Sass.</p>
<p>-- In a statement, Hambrecht &amp; Quist said it cut the rating to hold from buy and the 1997 earnings estimate to $0.53 a share from $0.60.</p>
<p>-- Hambrecht &amp; Quist said it had recommended the shares based partially on a successful sale to J.F. Lehman, and it is now concerned the new deal will divert attention from Computervision's core software business.</p>
</text>
